## Backend (`Backend/`)

Node.js + Express server written in TypeScript, using MongoDB (via Mongoose) for
storage and `express-session` (backed by `connect-mongo`) for cookie-based
authentication вЂ” no JWTs are actually issued despite `jsonwebtoken` being listed as
a dependency.

- **`Server.ts`** вЂ” The single file that defines every active route: auth
  (`/signup`, `/login`, `/logout`, `/me`), friends (`/friends/send`,
  `/friends/accept`, `/friends/decline`, `/friends`), messaging (`/messages`,
  `/messages/:contactId`), and file upload (`/upload`, via Multer). Also sets up
  CORS, the session middleware, and the MongoDB connection.
- **`Routes/`** вЂ” A parallel set of route files (`auth.ts`, `friendRoutes.ts`,
  `messageRoutes.ts`) written as separate Express Routers, mirroring the same
  logic as `Server.ts`. These are not imported or mounted anywhere вЂ” an
  in-progress refactor that was never wired in.
- **`models/`** вЂ” Mongoose schemas. `User.ts` handles password hashing
  automatically via a pre-save hook and tracks friends/incoming/sent requests as
  arrays of user references. `Message.ts` stores each message with optional
  text/image/audio/file URLs. `FriendRequest.ts` defines a separate
  request-tracking collection that isn't currently used anywhere in the app.
- **`uploads/`** вЂ” Where Multer saves uploaded files, named by upload timestamp;
  served statically at `/uploads/<filename>`.

## Frontend (`Frontend/`)

A Vite + React + TypeScript single-page app. Uses `axios` to call the backend API
and `@emoji-mart` for an emoji picker in the message composer. No router or
WebSocket library is included, based on the current dependency list.

- **`index.html`** / **`vite.config.ts`** вЂ” Vite's standard entry point and build
  configuration.
- **`index.css`** вЂ” Global styles, including rules that target the chat layout
  (contact sidebar, message bubbles, input bar) by matching inline `style`
  attributes on the React components.
- **`tsconfig*.json`** / **`eslint.config.js`** вЂ” Standard TypeScript project
  references and ESLint flat config for a Vite React app.
- **`src/`** вЂ” The actual application components and logic.

